title: [StatusQ] Can't build sandbox
body:
Running `scripts/build` fails with:

```
/home/rabbit/projects/status-im/StatusQ/sandbox/main.cpp:7:10: fatal error: qqmlsortfilterproxymodeltypes.h: No such file or directory
    7 | #include <qqmlsortfilterproxymodeltypes.h>
      |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
compilation terminated.
make[2]: *** [CMakeFiles/Sandbox.dir/build.make:2116: CMakeFiles/Sandbox.dir/main.o] Error 1
make[1]: *** [CMakeFiles/Makefile2:90: CMakeFiles/Sandbox.dir/all] Error 2
make: *** [Makefile:84: all] Error 2
```

@osmaczko Any idea what needs to be done to make this work?
I believe you miss [git submodule update --init](https://github.com/status-im/StatusQ/blob/master/README.md#using-command-line-interface)

@PascalPrecht compiles just fine under Linux:

```
[54/54 4.1/sec] Linking CXX executable sandbox/Sandbox
17:27:23: The process "/usr/bin/cmake" exited normally.
17:27:23: Elapsed time: 00:21.
```
Tried this with Cmake version `3.24.0-rc` and `3.22.5`

Prune your build dir completely, drop cmake cache, rerun cmake, ninja :)

```
ltinkl@zephyrus14:~$ cmake --version 
cmake version 3.22.2

CMake suite maintained and supported by Kitware (kitware.com/cmake).

ltinkl@zephyrus14:~$ ninja --version 
1.10.2
```
Yup done that. Doesn't do the trick. @osmaczko can support that claim :D
I had troubles compiling sandbox after the change to cmake as well. Just make sure you clean up EVERYTHING from the previous build, some qrc.o files etc, and then try again.
